# Tests

---

## Provider-T1 [G14] Read-only tools correctly report is_read_only()
**Status:** done
**Test File:** `backend/src/forge/tools.rs` (inline `#[cfg(test)]`)
**Tags:** stack:backend
**Depends on:** Provider-G1, Provider-D2

1. Create `ReadFileTool`, `SearchTool`, `ReadJadeTool`, `ListJadesTool`
2. Assert all return `is_read_only() == true`
3. Create `WriteFileTool`, `EditFileTool`, `ShellTool`, `WriteJadeTool`
4. Assert all return `is_read_only() == false`

- File-reading tools are classified as read-only.
- Writing and shell tools are classified as read-write.

